sentences: Olivia Jean Markel (born February 23, 1990) is an American singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist.
In 2009, Olivia received an invitation to record at Third Man Records in Nashville, Tennessee.
section: == Career == | === Jack White and Third Man Records ===

sentences: Jack White signed The Black Belles to Third Man Records and produced a handful of singles, as well as the bands debut self-titled album The Black Belles, released on October 8, 2011.
The band saw moderate success with touring; however, in 2012 the band was put on hiatus.
Her debut solo album, Bathtub Love Killings, was released in 2014 by Third Man Records.
Jean's second solo album, Night Owl was released on August 30, 2019 also on Third Man Records.
